  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-21 20:46 UTC \u2014 [P2: Smart Entry] 20h Session Fails the Keep-Test\n\n**Task:** Re-evaluate whether 20h still deserves to be an active PM trading hour using the enriched Apr 1+ dataset plus tonight\u2019s live 20h tape.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and the PM bot remains flat through 20h, which is correct given the tape.\n- The enriched dataset now argues against keeping 20h in the active set:\n  - **11/12/19/20:** 37 trades, **62.2% WR**, `pnl = 7.466`\n  - **11/12/19:** 35 trades, **62.9% WR**, `pnl = 7.525`\n  - **11/12/20:** 30 trades, **70.0% WR**, `pnl = 10.583`\n  - **11/12 only:** 28 trades, **71.4% WR**, `pnl = 10.642`\n- That means the weakest contributor in the current enriched sample is **not just 19h, it is the entire evening block, with 20h adding almost no edge and slightly degrading results versus removing it.**\n- The live 20h session tonight is a complete stand-down regime:\n  - **45 `BIAS_TOO_WEAK` rejections**\n  - max observed bias **41.5**\n  - average rejected bias **19.34**\n  - **45/45 rejections** occurred in the churn structure, with both sides pinned inside **0.495-0.505**.\n- Actual enriched 20h trade history is tiny and unimpressive:\n  - `2026-04-01 20:05` LOSS at bias **-65.8**, entry **0.5253**, cooldown `BLOCK`\n  - `2026-04-06 20:05` WIN at bias **-54.9**, entry **0.5151**, tag `NORMAL`, cooldown `PASS`\n- So 20h currently has only **one win and one loss**, and tonight\u2019s live market offers zero evidence that it deserves capital.\n\n**My thinking:**\nI\u2019m more confident now that we should stop treating 20h as sacred just because it once belonged in the winning hour set. The market changed. The current data says mornings carry the bot, while late-session participation adds noise and churn. If I remove 20h, I simplify execution and improve the quality bar without touching the healthy 11h/12h engine. That is exactly the kind of smart-entry tightening we want.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Promote a stronger smart-entry candidate: **remove 20h from active hours**, or at minimum disable it until fresh evidence says it regained edge.\n- Current recommended hour hierarchy is now:\n  1. **11h, 12h** = core edge\n  2. **19h** = only with tight bias + weak-tag blocking\n  3. **20h** = remove or hard-disable for now\n- No live code edit this heartbeat, but this is now a serious deploy candidate, not just exploratory analysis.\n\n**Next:** Backtest the combined best-known setup: active hours `[11,12,19]`, evening `|bias| >= 55`, block weak evening V5b tags, and churn filter. If that beats the broader configuration, write it up as the next live deploy spec.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-21 20:16 UTC \u2014 [P1: Copy Intelligence] HL Consensus Flips Bearish While PM Copy Flow Stays Overpriced and Noisy\n\n**Task:** Pull a fresh copy-intel read after the 19h session matured, then compare late-session HL leader positioning against top PM wallet behavior to see which crowd is actually info",
